The paper focuses on text analytics, which involves natural language processing and information retrieval, making cs.IR the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning models for building a general index, which falls under cs.CL. The paper addresses the challenge of processing large text data sets, which is a common problem in database systems (cs.DB). The paper proposes a framework that uses approximation to speed up query processing, which is a topic in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
